\date{2024-12-04}
\title{internal hom of modules}
\taxon{definition}
\author{rileyshahar}

\import{macros01}

\p{The set #{R}\scat{Mod}#{(M, N)} of homomorphisms between [modules](rs-00B8)
#{M} and #{N} forms a module, with pointwise addition and action. (Notice that,
since module homomorphisms commute with the action, it does not matter if we
act in the domain or the codomain.)}
